[{"text": "The story I wanted to share with you today", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is my challenge as an Iranian artist,", "start": 17.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "as an Iranian woman artist,", "start": 21.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as an Iranian woman artist", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "living in exile.", "start": 25.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, it has its pluses and minuses.", "start": 28.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "On the dark side,", "start": 31.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "politics doesn't seem to escape people like me.", "start": 33.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Every Iranian artist, in one form or another,", "start": 36.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is political.", "start": 39.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Politics have defined our lives.", "start": 41.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you're living in Iran,", "start": 44.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you're facing censorship, harassment,", "start": 46.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "arrest, torture --", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at times, execution.", "start": 51.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you're living outside like me,", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you're faced with life in exile --", "start": 56.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the pain of the longing", "start": 58.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the separation from your loved ones", "start": 60.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and your family.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Therefore, we don't find", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the moral, emotional,", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "psychological and political space", "start": 68.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to distance ourselves from the reality", "start": 70.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of social responsibility.", "start": 73.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Oddly enough,", "start": 76.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an artist such as myself", "start": 78.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "finds herself also in the position of being the voice,", "start": 80.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "the speaker of my people,", "start": 84.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even if I have, indeed,", "start": 87.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "no access to my own country.", "start": 89.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Also, people like myself,", "start": 92.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we're fighting two battles on different grounds.", "start": 95.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We're being critical of the West,", "start": 98.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the perception of the West", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about our identity --", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the image that is constructed about us,", "start": 104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about our women, about our politics,", "start": 107.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about our religion.", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We are there to take pride", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and insist on respect.", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And at the same time,", "start": 116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're fighting another battle.", "start": 118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That is our regime,", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our government --", "start": 122.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our atrocious government,", "start": 124.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "[that] has done every crime", "start": 126.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in order to stay in power.", "start": 128.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Our artists are at risk.", "start": 131.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We are in a position of danger.", "start": 134.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We pose a threat", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the order of the government.", "start": 139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But ironically,", "start": 141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this situation", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has empowered all of us,", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because we are considered, as artists,", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "central to the cultural, political,", "start": 149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "social discourse in Iran.", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We are there to inspire, to provoke,", "start": 154.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to mobilize,", "start": 157.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to bring hope to our people.", "start": 159.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We are the reporters of our people,", "start": 161.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and are communicators", "start": 164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the outside world.", "start": 166.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Art is our weapon.", "start": 168.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Culture is a form of resistance.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I envy sometimes the artists of the West", "start": 174.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for their freedom of expression.", "start": 177.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "For the fact that they can distance themselves", "start": 179.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from the question of politics.", "start": 182.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "From the fact that they are only serving one audience,", "start": 184.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "mainly the Western culture.", "start": 186.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But also, I worry about the West,", "start": 189.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "because often in this country,", "start": 193.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in this Western world that we have,", "start": 195.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "culture risks being a form of entertainment.", "start": 198.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Our people depend on our artists,", "start": 203.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and culture is beyond communication.", "start": 206.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "My journey as an artist", "start": 210.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "started from a very, very personal place.", "start": 212.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I did not start", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make social commentary", "start": 217.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about my country.", "start": 219.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The first one that you see in front of you", "start": 221.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is actually when I first returned to Iran", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after being separated for a good 12 years.", "start": 226.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It was after the Islamic Revolution", "start": 229.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of 1979.", "start": 231.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "While I was absent from Iran,", "start": 234.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Islamic Revolution had descended on Iran", "start": 237.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and had entirely transformed the country", "start": 240.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from Persian to the Islamic culture.", "start": 242.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I came mainly to be reunited with my family", "start": 245.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to reconnect in a way", "start": 248.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I found my place in the society.", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But instead, I found a country", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that was totally ideological", "start": 254.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that I didn't recognize anymore.", "start": 256.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "More so, I became very interested,", "start": 259.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as I was facing", "start": 261.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "my own personal dilemmas and questions,", "start": 263.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I became immersed in the study", "start": 265.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Islamic Revolution --", "start": 267.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "how, indeed,", "start": 269.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it had incredibly transformed", "start": 271.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the lives of Iranian women.", "start": 273.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I found the subject of Iranian women", "start": 275.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "immensely interesting,", "start": 277.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the way the women of Iran, historically,", "start": 279.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "seemed to embody the political transformation.", "start": 282.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So in a way, by studying a woman,", "start": 285.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you can read the structure and the ideology of the country.", "start": 288.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "So I made a group of work", "start": 292.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that at once faced my own personal questions in life,", "start": 294.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and yet it brought my work into a larger discourse --", "start": 298.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the subject of martyrdom,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the question of those who willingly stand in that intersection", "start": 303.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "of love of God, faith,", "start": 307.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "but violence and crime and cruelty.", "start": 311.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For me, this became incredibly important.", "start": 314.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And yet, I had an unusual position toward this.", "start": 317.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was an outsider", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who had come back to Iran to find my place,", "start": 322.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but I was not in a position", "start": 325.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be critical of the government", "start": 327.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or the ideology of the Islamic Revolution.", "start": 330.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This changed slowly", "start": 333.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as I found my voice", "start": 335.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I discovered things", "start": 337.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I didn't know I would discover.", "start": 339.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So my art became slightly more critical.", "start": 341.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "My knife became a little sharper.", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I fell into a life in exile.", "start": 346.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I am a nomadic artist.", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I work in Morocco, in Turkey, in Mexico.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I go everywhere to make believe it's Iran.", "start": 355.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now I am making films.", "start": 358.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Last year, I finished a film", "start": 360.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "called \"Women Without Men.\"", "start": 362.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Women Without Men\" returns to history,", "start": 364.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but another part of our Iranian history.", "start": 366.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It goes to 1953", "start": 369.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when American CIA exercised a coup", "start": 371.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and removed a democratically elected leader,", "start": 374.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Dr. Mossadegh.", "start": 376.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The book is written by an Iranian woman,", "start": 378.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Shahrnush Parsipur.", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a magical realist novel.", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This book is banned,", "start": 384.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and she spent five years in prison.", "start": 386.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "My obsession with this book,", "start": 388.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the reason I made this into a film,", "start": 390.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is because it at once was addressing", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the question of being a female --", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "traditionally, historically in Iran --", "start": 396.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the question of four women", "start": 399.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who are all looking for an idea", "start": 401.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of change, freedom and democracy --", "start": 403.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "while the country of Iran, equally, as if another character,", "start": 406.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "also struggled for an idea", "start": 409.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of freedom and democracy", "start": 411.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and independence from the foreign interventions.", "start": 413.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I made this film", "start": 416.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because I felt it's important", "start": 418.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for it to speak to the Westerners", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about our history as a country.", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That all of you seem to remember Iran", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after the Islamic Revolution.", "start": 427.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That Iran was once a secular society,", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and we had democracy,", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and this democracy was stolen from us", "start": 434.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the American government,", "start": 436.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the British government.", "start": 438.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This film also speaks to the Iranian people", "start": 440.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in asking them to return to their history", "start": 443.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and look at themselves before they were so Islamicized --", "start": 445.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "in the way we looked, in the way we played music,", "start": 449.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the way we had intellectual life.", "start": 452.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And most of all,", "start": 456.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the way that we fought for democracy.", "start": 458.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These are some of the shots actually from my film.", "start": 461.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These are some of the images of the coup.", "start": 464.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And we made this film in Casablanca,", "start": 466.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "recreating all the shots.", "start": 469.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This film tried to find a balance", "start": 471.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between telling a political story,", "start": 474.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but also a feminine story.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Being a visual artist, indeed,", "start": 478.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I am foremost interested to make art --", "start": 480.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to make art that transcends", "start": 483.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "politics, religion,", "start": 485.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the question of feminism,", "start": 487.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and become an important, timeless,", "start": 490.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "universal work of art.", "start": 492.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The challenge I have", "start": 494.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is how to do that.", "start": 496.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How to tell a political story but an allegorical story.", "start": 498.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "How to move you with your emotions,", "start": 501.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but also make your mind work.", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These are some of the images", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the characters of the film.", "start": 507.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now comes the green movement --", "start": 520.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the summer of 2009,", "start": 522.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as my film is released --", "start": 524.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the uprising begins in the streets of Tehran.", "start": 526.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What is unbelievably ironic", "start": 529.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the period that we tried to depict in the film,", "start": 532.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the cry for democracy", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and social justice,", "start": 537.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "repeats itself now", "start": 539.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "again in Tehran.", "start": 541.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The green movement", "start": 543.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "significantly inspired the world.", "start": 545.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It brought a lot of attention to all those Iranians", "start": 547.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who stand for basic human rights", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and struggle for democracy.", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What was most significant for me", "start": 554.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was, once again,", "start": 556.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the presence of the women.", "start": 558.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They're absolutely inspirational for me.", "start": 560.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If in the Islamic Revolution,", "start": 562.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the images of the woman portrayed", "start": 564.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were submissive", "start": 566.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and didn't have a voice,", "start": 568.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "now we saw a new idea of feminism", "start": 570.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the streets of Tehran --", "start": 572.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "women who were educated,", "start": 575.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "forward thinking, non-traditional,", "start": 577.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "sexually open, fearless", "start": 579.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and seriously feminist.", "start": 582.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These women and those young men", "start": 585.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "united Iranians", "start": 588.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "across the world, inside and outside.", "start": 590.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I then discovered", "start": 593.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why I take so much inspiration", "start": 595.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from Iranian women.", "start": 597.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That, under all circumstances,", "start": 599.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they have pushed the boundary.", "start": 601.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have confronted the authority.", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have broken every rule", "start": 605.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the smallest and the biggest way.", "start": 607.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And once again, they proved themselves.", "start": 609.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I stand here to say", "start": 611.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that Iranian women have found a new voice,", "start": 613.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and their voice is giving me my voice.", "start": 616.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it's a great honor", "start": 619.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be an Iranian woman and an Iranian artist,", "start": 621.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even if I have to operate in the West only for now.", "start": 624.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Thank you so much.", "start": 628.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 630.26, "duration": 8.0}]